.SH HASH ALGORITHM CATEGORIES
.SS Modern Secure Algorithms (Recommended)
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B bcrypt
\- Time-tested, widely supported, adjustable rounds
.IP \(bu 2
.B argon2, argon2i, argon2d
\- Memory-hard, modern standard (Password Hashing Competition winner)
.IP \(bu 2
.B pbkdf2
\- NIST recommended, widely supported
.IP \(bu 2
.B scrypt
\- Memory-hard, good for password storage
.RE
.SS SHA Family
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B sha256, sha512
\- Fast, general purpose hashing
.IP \(bu 2
.B sha3-256, sha3-512
\- Latest SHA standard
.IP \(bu 2
.B blake2b, blake2s
\- Fast secure hash functions
.RE
.SS Unix Crypt Format
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B crypt-sha512, unix-sha512
\- Standard Unix password format ($6$)
.IP \(bu 2
.B crypt-sha256, unix-sha256
\- Unix format ($5$)
.IP \(bu 2
.B crypt-md5, unix-md5
\- Legacy Unix format ($1$)
.RE
.SS Legacy (Not Recommended)
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B md5
\- Deprecated, use only for compatibility
.IP \(bu 2
.B whirlpool
\- Older algorithm, limited support
.RE
